ABUJA – Smear campaign war against the Governor of Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele, ahead of 2023 has been exposed. The Middle Belt Youths Forum (MBYF) had on Wednesday raised alarm over a plot to smear the image of Emefiele just to bully him from accepting to run for the 2023 Presidency. The group noted that the media and Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) have been recruited to damage his name. 2023 Presidency: Ajaokuta Branch Of Society Of Engineers Dumps… 2023: A Youth Can Do Better Than An Old Man – Atiku The MBYF alleged that they have uncovered that N10 billion has been earmarked by some disgruntled individuals to be spent on media campaigns against the Governor of CBN, Emefiele. The group, in a statement by its leader, Godwin Meliga, said there were plans to use the media and Civil Society Organisations to tarnish Emefiele’s image. The statement read: “We are aware of the ongoing highly-financed plot to use the media and CSOs to smear Emefiele’s name. “Our investigation revealed that the plot is to damage Emefiele’s name and bully him from accepting not to run for Presidency. “We, therefore, advise the media, individuals and groups to be wary of selfish individuals who may want to enlist them into the unpopular, inhuman and useless campaign that is meant to bully one of Nigeria’s and Africa’s best from the race that requires his expertise. POLL “We also urge Dr Emefiele not to be scared or distracted by this campaign that is destined to fail from conception.”